					<!-- ARCHETYPES -->
					<section class="archetypes-section">

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Brute</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Power & Proximity</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Dominance through power and proximity.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High STR/CON.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Close distance</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">trade blows</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">roar or charge when pressured</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Telegraph attacks clearly; reward clever positioning or staggering.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Urmine, Ironhide Boar
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Skirmisher</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Speed & Repositioning</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Speed, repositioning, and opportunistic strikes.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High DEX/INS.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Circle</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">jab</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">retreat</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">bait pursuit</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Burn hunter stamina through pursuit and distance control.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Cliff Strider, Ridge Wraith
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Kiter (Ranged Predator)</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Distance & Pressure</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Maintains distance; inflicts pressure through projectiles, breath, or traps.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High INS/DEX.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Keep line-of-sight</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">punish approach</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">relocate when cornered</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Play smart; use elevation and cover as survival tools.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Kragal, Sporeback Basilisk
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Ambusher</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Stealth & Burst</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Strikes when unseen; relies on camouflage or timing.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High INS/DEX.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Wait</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">isolate</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">burst</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">vanish</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">repeat</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Treat each strike as a story beat ‚Äî something learned or countered next time.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Noctilura, Mire Panther
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Guardian</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Territory & Defense</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Territorial and defensive; protects nests, zones, or lesser monsters.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> Very high CON, sometimes INS.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Hold ground</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">punish intrusion</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">enrage if home or allies are harmed</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Use lair actions and environmental control to emphasize dominance.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Terraguard Beetle, Hive Matron
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Shifter (Environmental Controller)</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Terrain & Chaos</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Alters terrain or weather mid-fight; thrives in chaos.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> Vary widely; often linked to INT or CON.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Manipulate environment</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">punish movement</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">adapt to new hazards</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Think of it as "fighting the arena as much as the monster."
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Stagmir, Sandwurm, Deep Coral Warden
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Tool User</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Intelligence & Adaptation</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Wields objects or exploits surroundings; demonstrates learned behavior.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High INT/INS.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Use tools to extend reach</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">adapt mid-fight</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">retreat to regroup if disarmed</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Give them "problem-solving" moments ‚Äî players should recognize evolving tactics.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Rockbreak Ape, Mud Sentinel
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Debuffer</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Status & Attrition</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Uses toxins, sounds, spores, or curses to cripple prey.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High CHA; often low CON.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Apply status</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">withdraw</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">harass weakened targets</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Don't overuse; one status effect per "phase" feels fair and cinematic.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Venom Toad, Frost Moth
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Support / Synergist</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Buff & Coordination</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Bolsters allies, heals, or enhances coordination.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> Moderate across board; relies on pack logic.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Buff or guard</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">reposition</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">rejoin alpha</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Use this archetype in multi-monster fights; they make the ecology feel alive.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Pack Howler, Hive Conductor
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Tactician (Pack Alpha)</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Command & Leadership</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Coordinates others; thrives in numbers.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> Balanced but with high INS/CHA (command presence).
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Command</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">delegate</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">punish isolation</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Give the alpha "pack reactions" ‚Äî when it howls or signals, others react.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Vorvarg Alpha, Frost Talon Matriarch
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Flyer</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Verticality & Range</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Controls verticality; dictates engagement range.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High DEX; moderate CON.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Scout</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">dive</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">retreat upward</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">strafe</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Let hunters "ground" flyers with terrain or timing to shift the phase.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Earule, Gale Wyvern
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Swimmer / Aquatic</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag">Water & Pressure</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Masters underwater or shoreline combat; controls oxygen and movement.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> High CON/STR.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Drag prey</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">drown</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">surface or ambush near edges</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Make terrain matter ‚Äî oxygen, currents, visibility.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Leviathan, Murkfin Croc
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="archetype-card apex-archetype">
							<div class="archetype-header">
								<h3>Intelligent / Apex Hybrid</h3>
								<span class="archetype-tag apex-tag">Multi-Archetype Mastery</span>
							</div>
							<div class="archetype-content">
								<div class="behavior">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Combines archetypes intelligently; recognizes patterns and adapts.
								</div>
								<div class="stats">
									<strong>Stats:</strong> All high; unique modifiers.
								</div>
								<div class="instinct-loop">
									<strong>Instinct Loop:</strong>
									<div class="loop-steps">
										<span class="step">Observe</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">counter</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">escalate</span>
										<span class="arrow">‚Üí</span>
										<span class="step">transform terrain or self</span>
									</div>
								</div>
								<div class="gm-tip">
									<strong>üé≤ GM Tip:</strong> Let it learn ‚Äî reward player pattern recognition with equal monster adaptation.
								</div>
								<div class="examples">
									<strong>Examples:</strong> Apex Wyvern, The Stagmir
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

					</section>

					<section class="usage-section">
						<h2>Using Archetypes</h2>
						<div class="usage-grid">
							<div class="usage-card">
								<h4>Standard Monsters</h4>
								<p>Use 1‚Äì2 archetypes to define clear behavioral identity. Example: A Fanged Beast might be Ambusher + Skirmisher.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="usage-card">
								<h4>Apex Monsters</h4>
								<p>Blend 3+ archetypes to create adaptive, intelligent predators. Example: An Elder Dragon could be Intelligent + Flyer + Shifter + Guardian.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="usage-card">
								<h4>Instinct Loops</h4>
								<p>Treat these as AI patterns, not strict scripts. Monsters should feel reactive and organic, not robotic.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="usage-card">
								<h4>GM Flexibility</h4>
								<p>Mix and match. A wounded Brute might shift to Ambusher tactics. Adaptation makes encounters memorable.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>

				</article>
			</div>
		</main>

